What you need to know:  With four Kenyans having been flagged for various violations of anti-doping rules at the Games, Kiptanui, who was placed fifth at Boston Marathon in April, and had personal best 2:05:47 from his victory in Xiamen Marathon last year, feared that he might be grouped with the dopers.“What makes me angry is that people ignore everything. People must take their work seriously,” said Kiptanui as he fought back tears.